  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "QC Inspector",
  "description": "<p>Support facility’s Repair business in quality control inspection and to ensure conformance and/or compliance to customers’, regulation & company requirements and, Global QA/BPA standard, procedure & process.<br /><br /><strong>PRIMARY RESPONSIBILITIES</strong></p><ul><li>Perform qualified NDE, visual & dimensional inspection (initial, in-process, final & Out-going QC inspection).</li><li>Provide QC report for all inspections in standard format & upload report in RigOffice (DMS).</li><li>Control of inspection tools and/or QC process equipment.</li><li>Maintain integrity & accuracy of process equipment used for test, inspection & report i.e. approved calibration, active calibration validity, acceptable tolerance etc.</li><li>Provide identification & traceability report of critical parts/items in standard format.</li><li>Witness, review & certify pressure test record, layout inspection (QP/ITP) and external work.</li><li>Report & record all nonconforming or quality issue for investigation/RCA on PIMS and to initiate the CAR/PAR to responsible Business Units Lead for quality improvement.</li><li>Perform other work-related tasks as assigned. </li><li>Comply with all NOV Company and HSE policies and procedures</li></ul><p><strong>EDUCATION & EXPERIENCE QUALIFICATIONS</strong></p><ul><li>Diploma in engineering or equivalent combination of education & experience in engineering field.</li><li>Certified NDE Level II Inspector ASNT-TC-1A or CWIP on MPI, LPI.</li><li>Experience working with ISO 9001/API-Q1 QMS standard</li><li>Experience of various inspection requirements- Welding, PMI-Materials, Quality Plan, Inspection Test Plan, NDE Methods, CMM-Dimension, International Standards i.e. API, ASME, ISO etc.</li><li>Good English written & communication.</li></ul>",
